  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "After your name and location, the religion was there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "This is, of course, has a great deal of implication in-- later on.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But-- so it was-- in the school, everybody know, naturally, what religion you are because you went to a different religious class.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And let's say, if there's fights-- some taking place, and you would hit someone then, then maybe they'd say, you dirty Jew, or something like that in order to somehow try to appear to be more important or something different.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, not necessarily.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I didn't look for preference on the base of religion.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, I, I, you know, I would assume that maybe some people do that way.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I never was-- made ever a major concern when I find my persons.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I think that's one of the tragedy of peoples.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They're looking some common denominator, which identify themselves being white, black, Jew, or Christian, rather the quality of the people I want to associate with.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we played on [LAUGHS] in the parks--",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--more than on the street.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh yes, oh, after-- when it was no school, and I finished my homework.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But then I was, of course, little, and every day at least twice.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was very interesting, you know, that-- I think this is-- I was very fortunate to be exposed to certain different kind of thinking.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And, you know, we've been talking about that Latin is a dead language, so to speak.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And what a waste to learn and study something of the past.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I think that, in order to understand our current situation and hoping for a better future, you have to know your past.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
